cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.NA, cs.GT. 

The paper deals with a geometric problem of computing maximal layers of a point set, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new data structure for storing and answering dominance queries, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem involves randomness, which suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as another possible sub-category. The algorithm's runtime is analyzed using probabilistic techniques, which is related to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the problem of computing maximal layers can be viewed as a game between two players, which is a topic in cs.GT (Game Theory).
